 The General Manager, Osun State Agency for Community and Social Development (CDSP), Mrs Funmi Aderonke Abokede, has said that the Community Driven Development (CDD) approach is the best way to ensure sustenance of donor-supported projects in the state. She said this during a training organised for CSDP desk officers drawn from Ministries, Departments and Agencies as well as all the local government areas in the state held in Osogbo, the state capital. Abokede described CDD as bottom-up approach that enables the beneficiaries of projects in their respective communities to partake actively in the process from conception to completion stage. Abokede charged local government chairmen in the state to embrace the CDD approach to ensure effectiveness of the projects in their respective local government areas. She commended the state governor, Mr Rauf Aregbesola, for his prompt payment of counterpart funds which has made the state to benefit very well from donor-supported projects. She explained that the training was aimed at equipping CSDP desk officers on CDD as the right approach development.   The General Manager, Osun CSDP, Mrs Funmi Aderonke Abokede Abokede highlighted the pragmatic approaches to engaging stakeholders on donor-supported projects in their community and ensure that they are fully involved.  Also, the Osun CSDP Operation Manager, Mr Felix Akinwande; Monitoring and Evaluation Manager, Mr Ademola Adeyemo and the Project Officer Supervisor, Engineer Abiodun Oparinde in separate presentation buttressed Abokede's position and charged the desk officers to familiarize themselves with the new strategy.